<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 02 at 4:56PM MDT until July 02 at 5:30PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 530 PM MDT
FOR EAST CENTRAL PRAIRIE AND SOUTHWESTERN DAWSON COUNTIES...
At 455 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles southwest
of Lindsay, or 19 miles north of Terry, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Marsh.
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
